  <description type="morphology">Stems branched distally, terete to 5-ridged, to 200 cm. Leaves: length and width of those on main stem 2 times or more those on branches; stipules with stipular sheaths not inflated, 1.2--3.4 cm, ligule 0.2--1.1 cm; blade linear, 5--21 cm &amp;#180; 0.4--5.1 (--8.5) mm, apex apiculate, cuspidate, or rarely round; veins 3--5. Inflorescences: peduncles axillary, rarely terminal, erect to ascending, cylindric, 1.2--5.2 cm; spikes cylindric, rarely moniliform, 13--45 mm; verticels 4--9. Fruits brown to reddish brown, obovoid to oblanceoloid, 3--3.9 &amp;#180; 2.8--3 mm; beak toward abaxial margin, erect or rarely recurved to apex, 0.2--0.3 mm. Chromosome number apparently unknown.not available.</description>
